## 💡 Tips for Non-Technical Users

- You only ever need to copy and paste the commands above.
- You can re-run commands at any time — they won't break anything.
- Everything you create lives in simple Markdown files (like Google Docs you can version).
- You can always edit or improve files directly in Cursor.
- If you get stuck, scroll up to the command you just ran — the terminal tells you exactly where files were created.

